summary:
River systems and their sedimentary records are my main interest. Of course from source to sink - so all the way from the headwaters, through their valleys into their deltas and estuaries. Currently, I'm researching the Nile River in Egypt and Sudan, and the greater African Sahel region. 

I'm a self-motivated Quaternary Geologist with a keen eye for detail and result-oriented solutions. A key component throughout my recent work is setting up, supervising and executing international fieldworks in close collaboration with local organisations and globally recognized colleagues and institutions.

Specialisms: Quaternary Geology, Geomorphology, Sedimentology, Geoarchaeology, Dating techniques, GIS, Remote Sensing, Geological mapping and Field work.
